title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer 556 HOLO Edition Semi Auto Rifle
postcontent: Up for AUCTION is a Sig Sauer 556 HOLO Edition 5.56mm N.A.T.O./.223 Semi Automatic Rifle. If you would like to own the finest gas piston system AR rifle on the market, this is it. Purchased this from an uncle who never fired the weapon, and I have fired approx. 150 rounds through it without a single jam/malfunction. The rifle should be considered USED/Like New, absolutely excellent condition. Must say the original Sig HOLO reflex sight that came with it was not highest quality. Sold it and replaced with Tru-Glo Red Dot, much better quality. Rifle will come with one 30rd., and one 20rd. metal mag. The SIG556® HOLO features the same high-performance two position adjustable gas piston operating rod system engineered by Swiss Arms and marries it to a CNC machined from 7075-T6 grade aluminum forged trigger housing that not only cuts the rifle’s weight by a pound but is designed to accept standard AR magazines. The SIG556 HOLO features a 16” military grade COLD HAMMER FORGED BARREL, chambered in 5.56mm NATO, with a twist rate of 1 in 7”. The SIG556 HOLO has a proven two position adjustable gas piston operating rod system joined to a lightweight alloy trigger housing that accepts standard AR magazines. The vented non-slip polymer forearm has three Picatinny rails for accessory mounting. Sight options include front combat sight, flip-up rear sight, and a red dot style holographic sighting system that allows for quick target acquisition, with four illuminated reticle patterns with adjustable intensities. The SIG556 buttstock is collapsible and has a rubber butt pad and a number of sling attachment points. Select versions feature a folding stock with the ability to collapse, providing the best of both worlds. Rifle will be shipped in a cardboard box, with the Sig padded hard plastic case it originally came in. I could not locate owners manual, but copy of disassembly/assembly is included. Full owners manual is available at www.sigsauer.com. Shipping fee of $35.00 will be paid by winner of auction, signature by receiving FFL will be required on either USPS Priority, or UPS ground. Rifle ships when funds clear. No shipping to, or purchase by residents of CA, NY, or MA. My FFL that will ship is Jeremy Zdzinicki of LWZ Firearms, LLC. He is listed at Gunbroker, just search Illinois zip code 60468, and advise your FFL for contact info. Illinois residents need only provide valid F.O.I.D. CAA is proud to introduce the new Clear Action Magazine. This unique magazine provides both a clear window on the side showing the number of rounds rem aining in the magazine and a full magazine indicator button on the bottom. The clear window on the magazine side allows the user to easily view the number of rounds remaining, corresponding to the numbers stamped into the body. In addition a white full magazine indicator on the bottom pops out of the magazine base, providing a tactile indicator of a fully loaded magazine during low light or night operations. A non-tilting follower and stainless steel spring produces a magazine you can count on for 100% reliability. With the clear window showing you the remaining rounds at a glance, and the full magazine indicator, you now have a superior design, executed flawlessly, resulting in your tactical advantage.

title: For Sale/Trade:  RARE 1903 Webley Mk IV Boer War .45 Revolver
postcontent:
Very rare webley revolver for sale.  This is a "Boer War" model that saw service in South Africa in the wars that followed the Zulu war.  This has the rare "birds head" grip, and proof marks from when it was issued and re-issued to different regiments.  Very cool historical piece.

Has ALL MATCHING SERIALS.
has NO IMPORT MARKINGS

It is complete, locks up reasonably well.  It HAS unfortunately been shaved from the original .455 eley caliber so that it can work with 45acp and 45ar cases.  This was typical of surplus webley revolvers after wwii.  If it hadn't been shaved, it would likely be worth 2x.  This really is more of an antique collectible, but is certainly shootable.  It has some pits and some wear in the barrel from being 110 years old.  It looks like it was refinished at some point, as the current blueing is strong, and was obviously done over some of the cleaned up pits.  Overall, very nice condition for its age.

Why am I selling?  I'm downsizing my collection and this one doesn't ever go to the range.  It was(is) a hard decision to let this go, as I've never seen another like it in my life.

Pictures are here:  http://s406.beta.photobucket.com/user/andrewschwabe/library/firearms/webley-mk-iv

Asking price is $900 or best reasonable offer.  This is a very rare piece in great condition and is shootable.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Shelby Cobra collector electric guitar custom by Jarrett, signed by Carroll Shelby
postcontent:
I also am looking to pay ca$h for a couple of AR's to keep up at my place in the mountains, I won't waste your time and won't low ball you, I'll buy at a fair price.  If you are testing the market or trying to sell $999.00 Walmart AR's for $1200+ don't bother, they will be $999.00 again once the idiot's get out of the game and I will wait it out, makes no difference to me.  But, if you have bills to pay and don't want to deal with lookie loo's, then email me and we can make an easy painless deal...  

Also, click on "Listings by this user" for my Rolex I am looking to trade also...  ON TO THE GUTAR

This is an extremely rare opportunity to own an unique item. First off, the electric guitar was made by Jarrett Guitars, 50 guitars were scheduled to be built in the limited "Commemorative Series" and this is guitar number #19 in the series, serial number CSX2002-34, but only 40 ended up making the production run from what I have found out.  The Guitar comes with certificate of authenticity from JARRETT GUITARS, CONNECTICUT USA, authenticated by Jack Camarda.  All of this can be verified by contacting Mr. Camarda at Jarrett, he was the program's director, he actually returned my call when I was researching the Guitar almost 10 years ago when I bought it.  (You can google his name & Shelby Guitar, and get the history of the project).  

Anyways, it's a rare piece both for collectors and players, and an extremely unique piece for Shelby Cobra fans. 22 frets, humbuckers, 3 way selector switch. Volume and tone controls push/pull to split the coils in the humbuckers. Set neck with pearl inlays, and custom Shelby Cobra graphics. If you Google this guitar and read the Harmony Central reviews, you will discover just how amazing this guitar really is. This guitar has lived it's life in it's case which is included. The guitars originally sold in the 4k-8k range due to the limited number made and have never seen one that was autographed, period.

As for the autograph, being a Shelby Cobra owner I have attended several events at Boulder, Colorado's "Shelby American Collection" museum.  Mr. Shelby signed this at one of the annual Christmas benefits (December, 2007) and all monies collected from the benefits were donated to help operate the museum and to the Carroll Shelby Foundation (http://www.cscf.org/). As such it comes with a certificate of authenticity from them. I had Mr. Shelby inscribe it to me and my name can easily be removed if you want me to remove it.  Just takes some rubbing alcohol because the inscribed signature was done with a Sharpie and since the guitars finish has several layers of clear coat built up on it, the Sharpie couldn't have penetrated through the finish. I am the original owner of the guitar and have owned it for almost 10 years. I have rarely come across these guitars and have never seen one that has been autographed. As you know Mr. Shelby has passed away and therefore I wouldn't anticipate a signed example making it to the market..

To get an idea of value's you can check out these current auctions for similar guitars, first ones aren't autographed, second one is signed but a different style of Shelby Guitar. It's just to give an idea, I don't need any insulting low ball offers, I paid a lot of money just for the guitar...

This Marine said what I know all of us gun owners & freedom lovers think, in a very clear unambiguous way to the people who live under the freedom REAL men have fought to provide for them. Then, people like FiendStein TAX & REGULATE us to death, while she & her husband get rich on our dime!!

I served in the US Air Force (1967-71) when NO HOMOS or Nancy boys were alowed in ANY branch of service and guns were NOT the so called problem!

*********************************************************************

"Senator Dianne Feinstein,
 I will not register my weapons should this bill be passed, as I do not believe it is the government’s right to know what I own. Nor do I think it prudent to tell you what I own so that it may be taken from me by a group of people who enjoy armed protection yet decry me having the same a crime. You ma’am have overstepped a line that is not your domain. I am a Marine Corps Veteran of 8 years, and I will not have some woman who proclaims the evil of an inanimate object, yet carries one, tell me I may not have one.

 I am not your subject. I am the man who keeps you free. I am not your servant. I am the person whom you serve. I am not your peasant. I am the flesh and blood of America.

 I am the man who fought for my country. I am the man who learned. I am an American. You will not tell me that I must register my semi-automatic AR-15 because of the actions of some evil man.

 I will not be disarmed to suit the fear that has been established by the media and your misinformation campaign against the American public.

 We, the people, deserve better than you.

 Respectfully Submitted,
 Joshua Boston
 Cpl, United States Marine Corps
 2004-2012"
